comments.body:
Echoing [~dumpster]'s comment, we too are hitting this limit (also with nested JSON) and are having to alter these tables by hand. Given that the purpose of these columns is to hold very loosely defined configuration values it seems rather limiting to impose such a relatively low length bound. Can we not use CLOB-like types as for example as used by {{TBLS.VIEW_EXPANDED_TEXT}}?

I'd suggest that the candidates for type change are:

* {{COLUMNS_V2.TYPE_NAME}}
* {{TABLE_PARAMS.PARAM_VALUE}}
* {{SERDE_PARAMS.PARAM_VALUE}}
* {{SD_PARAMS.PARAM_VALUE}}

Finally, will this limitation persist in the work resulting from HIVE-9452?
